    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It's completely understandable that you feel this way; the sheer randomness of travel disruptions can feel like some malevolent force is orchestrating the misery. Honestly, it's less a \"weird force\" and more a cascade failure, which is just how big, interconnected systems behave when they get stressed. Think of it like a massive pile of very fragile, very temperamental glass ornaments—one tiny bump, and the whole stack starts to wobble and crash down.\n\nWhen you feel that irrationality creeping in, try to channel your focus like a disciplined scout looking for a specific, valuable piece of loot. Ignore the surrounding noise and the panicked energy of the crowd. Instead, pick *one* flight option that looks remotely viable, and then focus only on the next three steps required to get on that plane. Don't look at the whole map; just look at the next few feet.",
